"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Wyoming, one of the leading states for blockchain innovation, is also offering education on DeFi to students at the University of Wyoming. Ali Nejadmalayeri, a professor of finance at the University of Wyoming, told Cointelegraph that the university offers a blockchain minor and that various disciplines within the sector can be studied as courses.\\n\\nFor example, Nejadmalayeri teaches the Blockchain and Financial Services course, which is a full-semester online class that contains a portion on DeFi concepts:\\n\\n> “The first part of this course during the Spring semester focused on an introduction and review of the blockchain sector. The second module was about the digital money sphere, which included early experimentation of electronic money and central bank digital currencies. DeFi was the last portion, where we discussed platforms like Uniswap and Aave, along with various applications.”\\n\\nAccording to Nejadmalayeri, anyone globally can take the Blockchain and Financial Services course. “If you are admitted as a non-traditional student then you can take the course,” he explained, adding that about 10 students took the class during the Spring semester. But given the interest in DeFi, he expects that number to grow moving forward, pointing out that individuals who don’t have a computer science or finance background are starting to find DeFi interesting:\",\"timestamp\":1639035563,\"title\":\"Wyoming, one of the leading states for blockchain innovation\"},\"digest\":\"54Jw-fzKlCiEaeeu-i1PwoVNsc0bLm6e1thhBj3QNhI\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x9E1eD0a565710397B9d0Fb0716dCBe1eC41fdbD8\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"asy-zcQvgN0cJLMxowtbM4LMgZXODdDCEkaL1RjpDOU\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"mdLxHFn7OH7SBvCz14LlvPuk-muQb8S5LSrou0ogAx0\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"nd3Fs22mHZV6qhwQuvPTpsyaZ9DKqNLaUoKHs1qdzgPPMpsDRYwhCBC3D76Q9Yj8g2BKWBvPmFuoEXv_YzjzrQ\",\"